abstract.text: Continuation to be invoked once the interceptor is done processing a request. If invoked with a HttpRequest, the
HTTP service will proceed to make a request via the network. Invoking the continuation with a HttpResponse bypasses
the network and causes the request to complete immediately with the specified response. The ID of the HttpResponse
is irrelevant in this case.
Contains either an HttpRequest or an HttpResponse.
